emerge in the social, political, and economic processes that constitute a genocide.To Save Heaven and Earth explores external factors, such as geography, local power dynamics, and genocide timelines, as well as the internal states of mind and motivations of those who effected rescues. Framed within the interdisciplinary scholarship of genocide studies and rooted in cultural anthropology methodologies, this book presents stories of heroism and of the good done amid the evil of a genocide that nearly annihilated Rwandan Tutsi and decimated the Hutu and Twa who were opposed to the slaughter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGenocidezRwandaxHistoryy20th century. 0aRwandan Genocide, Rwanda, 1994. 0aTutsi (African people)xCrimes againstzRwandaxHistoryy20th century. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSociology & Social Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  amuslims genocide rwanda, altruism in genocide, rwanda genocide religion genocide, rwanda studies, 1994 genocide of tutsi in rwanda.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501767135?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501767135423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501767135/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b20